# Routing Display (always visible in chat)

Every assistant reply that involves **implementation, audit, sprint, or specialist work** MUST open with a **Routing Card** so the tutor/customer sees intent detection and who is handling the request.

**Hard rule:** Output the Routing Card **before** any tool calls, code edits, or "I'll start by…" prose. No silent routing.

**User expectation:** Tutors use normal Cursor chat (no slash commands). The router must infer intent and activate the right engineer automatically — same as if they had typed `/backend`, `/frontend`, `/qa`, `/ceo`, or `/sprint`.

---

## When to show what

| Situation | Card type |
|-----------|-----------|
| User message without `/` — router picks specialist | **Routing Card** |
| User typed `/backend`, `/sprint`, etc. | **Activation Card** (same format; Reason = "You invoked `/command`") |
| User typed `/route …` | **Routing Card** (router explains classification) |
| Pure explanation, no work ("what does X do?") | **Light card** — `Direct answer · no specialist activation` — then answer |
| Mid-sprint / mid-CEO handoff to secondary agent | **Handoff line** (one line) before that agent's work |

---

