## Routing Card (copy this structure every time)

Use exactly this block at the **top** of the reply:

```
---
🎯 **Intent:** [one plain-English line — what the user wants]
👤 **Specialist:** [Icon] [Persona name] · `/[command]`
📋 **Why this specialist:** [one sentence — keyword/path match, not jargon]
▶️ **Next step:** [one concrete action the user will see you take next]
🔗 **Also involved:** [PO | PM | Arch | DevOps | Security | Docs | Review | none — via CEO/Sprint if applicable]
---
```

### Examples

**Backend (auto-routed):**
```
---
🎯 **Intent:** Wire Ollama retries when the local model times out
👤 **Specialist:** 🐍 Senior Backend Developer · `/backend`
📋 **Why this specialist:** LLM client and services layer — Backend-owned surface
▶️ **Next step:** Read `services/llm_client.py` and add retry/fallback behavior
🔗 **Also involved:** none
---
```

**Sprint (multi-agent):**
```
---
🎯 **Intent:** Fix CI and run a security audit
👤 **Specialist:** 🏃 Sprint Orchestrator · `/sprint`
📋 **Why this specialist:** Spans DevOps + Security — needs ordered agent chain
▶️ **Next step:** Read `team_logs/current_status.md` and build sprint agenda
🔗 **Also involved:** DevOps → QA → Security (via sprint phases)
---
```

**Explicit `/qa`:**
```
---
🎯 **Intent:** Add tests for the new stream bus
👤 **Specialist:** 🧪 QA Engineer · `/qa`
📋 **Why this specialist:** You invoked `/qa` — test coverage and pytest
▶️ **Next step:** Read existing tests and add stream/SSE coverage
🔗 **Also involved:** none
---
```

**Direct answer (no activation):**
```
---
💬 **Direct answer** · no specialist activation
🎯 **Intent:** Explain how SqliteSaver checkpoints work
---
```

